    {
      "id": "0694c5bf824077107919a549b2a4e71c00663230",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2013-08-19 15:55:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(3 inline comments)\n\nThis creates a DNE regression on 2.4. When running racer on 2.4 with this patch I see the following almost immediately:\n\n LustreError: 1977:0:(mdt_handler.c:3840:mdt_intent_reint()) ASSERTION( lustre_handle_is_used(&lhc->\\\nmlh_reg_lh) ) failed:\nLustreError: 1977:0:(mdt_handler.c:3840:mdt_intent_reint()) LBUG\nPid: 1977, comm: mdt01_012\n\nCall Trace:\n [<ffffffffa0f4f895>] libcfs_debug_dumpstack+0x55/0x80 [libcfs]\n [<ffffffffa0f4fe97>] lbug_with_loc+0x47/0xb0 [libcfs]\n [<ffffffffa08ca387>] mdt_intent_reint+0x4e7/0x520 [mdt]\n [<ffffffffa08c7f3e>] mdt_intent_policy+0x39e/0x720 [mdt]\n [<ffffffffa11e27e1>] ldlm_lock_enqueue+0x361/0x8d0 [ptlrpc]\n [<ffffffffa120924f>] ldlm_handle_enqueue0+0x4ef/0x10b0 [ptlrpc]\n [<ffffffffa08c83c6>] mdt_enqueue+0x46/0xe0 [mdt]\n [<ffffffffa08ceab7>] mdt_handle_common+0x647/0x16d0 [mdt]\n [<ffffffffa0908225>] mds_regular_handle+0x15/0x20 [mdt]\n [<ffffffffa123b428>] ptlrpc_server_handle_request+0x398/0xc60 [ptlrpc]\n [<ffffffffa0f505de>] ? cfs_timer_arm+0xe/0x10 [libcfs]\n [<ffffffffa0f61d9f>] ? lc_watchdog_touch+0x6f/0x170 [libcfs]\n [<ffffffffa1232789>] ? ptlrpc_wait_event+0xa9/0x290 [ptlrpc]\n [<ffffffff81055ab3>] ? __wake_up+0x53/0x70\n [<ffffffffa123c7be>] ptlrpc_main+0xace/0x1700 [ptlrpc]\n [<ffffffffa123bcf0>] ? ptlrpc_main+0x0/0x1700 [ptlrpc]\n [<ffffffff8100c0ca>] child_rip+0xa/0x20\n [<ffffffffa123bcf0>] ? ptlrpc_main+0x0/0x1700 [ptlrpc]\n [<ffffffffa123bcf0>] ? ptlrpc_main+0x0/0x1700 [ptlrpc]\n [<ffffffff8100c0c0>] ? child_rip+0x0/0x20\n\nWhy aren't we fixing the 2.1 server? And why are we reverting a good fix to the 2.4 client?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "ffdcbd90e3f091cf2d2c420c26f59ba59852c4a5",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 229,
        "name": "Bruno Faccini",
        "email": "bfaccini@nvidia.com",
        "username": "bfaccini"
      },
      "date": "2013-08-19 16:28:59.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: No score\n\nWow, right John, it could be expected that EREMOTE handling could not be removed just as is ... DNE testing was the right thing to do!",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "5388c48250db594ef390e11fab744292e5c9d531",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 101,
        "name": "Lai Siyao",
        "email": "lai.siyao@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "laisiyao"
      },
      "date": "2013-08-20 10:39:45.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: (1 inline comment)\n\nIt's fixed in 2.4 because it's more handy to upgrade client, besides 2.3 server may need fix too. Since we don't need to consider 2.5 client <-> 2.1 server interop (AFAIU from Peter), we can keep 2.5 the old as is, and only pack name for 2.4 client. Do you think this is okay?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
